HEADWORD: Sluicy
<hw>Slui`cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Falling copiously or
in streams, as from a sluice.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And oft whole sheets descend of <qex>sluicy</qex> rain.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

